script = ExtResource("3_kiwau")
category = 1
text = "Gus, or the \"Sword of the Seas\" is a Legendary Gira from the present era, with many thinking he is the most powerful Sugori alive. Gus is a veteran pirate and captain of the Valiant Pirates, a Gira crew who have well balanced power and popularity. He has been a Gira for 38 years and started his pirate journey at the low age of 14.

Not much is known about his background, he decides to keep it hidden for the sake of his family's privacy. None of his immediate family are or were pirates. This was the reason for why he was a bit of a troubled kid. He keeps his surname hidden, only close crew members know it. Gus has been asked if he has any kids, he did not answer the question, but merely said if he does it would be obvious. Gus in his younger years was still strong, after being noticed on his home island, the Great Fumbrian Pirates picked him up and trained him. He even dueled young Scareye at the age of 17, and gave him his signature scar. Scareye once said the only man who he would not want to fight is Gus, and that \"age does not hinder that demon's ability\". The captain of this crew, Jay \"The Warship\" Rocks who was a Legendary Gira at the time, was a personal mentor for Gus and valued pirates having their own journeys. So after 4 years of training, Gus left them to start his own crew where he collected not many pirates but only those he deemed worthy in strength. In only a year, Gus would gain the rank of Gira after the retirement of \"Grizzly\" John Ranford and travel the seas protecting the Sugori for the 38 years until now.

The Valiant Pirates are a very loyal pirate crew, with many members sticking by his side for 40 years. He has 5 commanders that have their own ship if need be and they all are really consistent fighters. The most notable is Dante Birdman, his Right Hand who even has immense respect from Vanessa Haliness herself. Gus has had many powerful pirates under his wing at one point, he trained: Destiny the Pirate Prodigy, Jack Hawk the Joloise alongside 3 other Joloise Captains, Hrurdin Mopp before he became King Warrior Nidon the Restless' Right Hand Man, and many other minor recruits. Gus enjoys recruiting young talent he notices on his journeys, and then trains them to be good pirates and lets them have a journey of his own like what Rocks did.

All of the Gira's coincidentally have a unique fighting style, Gus is the only swordsman of the four. Gus has two swords called Sodom & Gomorrah, they are curved cutlasses which have handles of Sugori gold, gifted to him by ex-Mala Earl Haliness VI. Gus has prolific sword offence and defence, and can guard most things with his swords. He got taught sword combat by his ex-captain Jay Rocks, but later awakened his real sword powers after finding out his ancesters were swordsmen. Therefore, Gus uses the technique of \"Wind Fighting\", which is a supposedly ancient sword fighting technique passed down by his ancestors. Yet he does not know he is using Wind Magic and his distant ancestors were settlers from the Central continent Volin.

Gus has himself stopped 7 invasions single handedly with no Gira or Army support. He has confirmed to have arrested 3100 criminals and up-to-no-good travellers. Gus is known for his aggressive style of navy combat but even with such a riskee tactical approach, he has yet to lose a battle. His most important encounter was in the Bullgrave Incident, where he had to defend the border from Scareye. Recently, Gus was under huge regional fire with the Elitrics for capturing one of their spies, but he caught their bluffs. One day 23 years ago, a witch called Gildred met Gus when he was resting in a coastal island of Sugori. Supposedly, Gildred is a traveller that wishes to give powerful warriors magical powers, Gus ended up declining."
id = 1
name = "Gus"
gdscript = ExtResource("1_ywv7u")
